---
description: Preserve repository line endings
alwaysApply: true
---

# Line Endings

- Preserve the existing line-ending style of every file you edit.
- In this repository on Windows, prefer `CRLF` for new text files unless nearby files or explicit repo configuration require a different style.
- Avoid introducing line-ending-only diffs unless the user explicitly asks for normalization.
- If a file already uses a consistent EOL style, keep that style unchanged after edits.

# File Formatting When Editing

- Match the **line density** of the target file and its nearest sibling (e.g. other `CMakeLists.txt` in the repo): one newline between consecutive lines, blank lines only between logical sections.
- **Never** insert a blank line after every source line. That often happens when reconstructing content from Read-tool output with line numbers — do not do that.
- Prefer `StrReplace` on the exact existing span for small edits. Use `Write` only for new files or full rewrites; when rewriting, copy structure from a sibling file, not from formatted chat/read output.
- After editing a file, if `git diff` shows every line changed with no logical edits, stop and fix line endings/spacing before continuing.
